Sculptor->Branch

"Branch" is a tool which provides a method of building "branched
objects" stemming out of the base object..  The branch tool is used in
conjunction with "Potter" and other "Sculptor" tools . Branch can be
used to create "hierarchically linked" objects such as coffee cup
handles, animal legs or arms, heads, door knobs and so on.

The branch of an object is constrained to be at a certain position on
the main object's body. Even if the shape of the object or its branch
is changed, this constraint is maintained.

"Branch" has two active modes:

"Create New": Choose "Create New", then go into the viewer window and
click a point on the object. This will immediately sprout a new branch
object (default Potter object) at that point. You can now move the
branch in a single direction in and out of the main object. This
allows you to "bury" the branch at a given distance to avoid seams. If
you have an existing branch selected before choosing "Create New", you
can click a new point on the object. The branch will now be
repositioned at the new spot.

"Edit Old": Select an existing branch of the main object, and choose
"Edit Old". You can now "rebury" the branch with respect to the main
object.

"Remove": Select a branch of the main object, and choose "Remove".
That will remove the "branch" connection. That is, the two objects are
no longer constrained to each other. (You can now delete the branch
altogether by using "Cut").

